Pregnant? Stay up to date with your #COVID19 vaccines. Data show that completing an mRNA COVID-19 vaccine series (Pfizer-BioNTech or Moderna) while pregnant can help protect your baby from hospitalization. Get vaccinated against COVID-19. Read more: https://t.co/pBVlI6STf8.

Most reinfection cases happened among people who were not up to date on #COVID19 vaccinations. All eligible people should stay up to date on their vaccines for increased protection and should consider retesting if exposed to COVID-19 or have symptoms. https://t.co/UnOVDIkFo6.

New @CDCMMWR study found some people can be reinfected with #COVID19 shortly after initial infection. To best protect against reinfection, everyone ages 5+ years should stay up to date on their COVID-19 vaccines. Learn more: https://t.co/8ErtcC9koH. https://t.co/ULp54mXRq7

Most people who get very sick w/ #COVID19 during pregnancy aren’t vaccinated. mRNA COVID-19 vaccines (Pfizer-BioNTech & Moderna) lower risk of infection & severe illness. If you’re pregnant or trying to be, stay up to date on your COVID-19 vaccines. More: https://t.co/pBVlI7au6G.
